-- Typo-binder hint: lowercase `nothing` is NOT the constructor NOTHING —
-- it silently binds everything. Case-insensitive equality fires the hint
-- at any name length. Never blocking (SInfo).
GIVEN m IS A MAYBE NUMBER
GIVETH A NUMBER
f m MEANS
  CONSIDER m
  WHEN JUST x THEN x
  WHEN nothing THEN 0

#EVAL f (JUST 5)
